# Auto-Save Workflow

## CRITICAL: After EVERY Code Change
After making any code change (no matter how small), ALWAYS do all three steps:
1. **Build**: `npx vite build` — verify no errors
2. **Git**: `git add -A && git commit -m "..." && git push origin feature/api-integration`
3. **iCloud**: `rsync -av --exclude='node_modules' --exclude='.git' --exclude='dist' "Evair-H5/" "~/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/Evair-H5-Backup/"`

Do NOT ask the user for permission to push. Just do it automatically.

## CRITICAL: Context Persistence
This project has been developed over a month across many sessions. To preserve institutional knowledge:

### Where Context Lives
- **Cursor rules** (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`): Auto-loaded in every chat. Contains architecture, decisions, API docs, deployment workflow.
- **Conversation history** (`docs/CONVERSATION_HISTORY.md`): Detailed log of all sessions, decisions, and changes.
- **Git log**: Every commit has descriptive messages. Use `git log` to see recent history.
- **Agent transcripts**: Cursor auto-saves full chat transcripts.

### When to Update Context Files
Update the cursor rules AND `docs/CONVERSATION_HISTORY.md` when:
- A new feature is implemented
- A business decision is made
- A bug fix reveals important context
- Architecture or UX patterns change
- The user explicitly asks to save

### What to Update
- `project-overview.mdc`: File structure, UI/UX decisions, business rules
- `business-decisions.mdc`: Strategy decisions, feature removals, billing/supplier info
- `esim-api-services.mdc`: API changes, new endpoints, data flow changes
- `deployment.mdc`: Git workflow, environment changes
- `docs/CONVERSATION_HISTORY.md`: Add a new dated section with all changes

## Lessons Learned (Apply These Always)
- When changing a status badge/label in one place, check ALL places that display the same status (banner card, detail card, network status row)
- When fixing spacing/padding, use shared CSS classes (`.pt-safe`) instead of one-off inline styles
- Always test build before committing
- The user's phone browser (Netlify) and Cursor browser (localhost) have separate localStorage — test purchases don't sync across devices
- Chinese IT staff instructions should be written in Chinese
- Explain technical decisions clearly so the user can relay to their team
